elements.title: Lisa Winter (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Lisa Winter (pictured) took part in robot battles at 10 years old?

elements.title: Fermi 1 (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the sodium fast reactor Fermi 1 suffered a nuclear meltdown that led one operator to suggest "we almost lost Detroit"?

elements.title: Rosina Buckman (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that when soprano Rosina Buckman returned to New Zealand for a concert tour in 1922, the prime minister and a former prime minister spoke at the reception?

elements.title: Chester A. Congdon (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the freighter Chester A. Congdon became the largest financial loss to date on the Great Lakes when she wrecked in 1918?

elements.title: International Habitation Module (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that ESA astronauts used virtual reality to verify the design of the International Habitation Module?

elements.title: Stephen Bishop (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Stephen Bishop's 1842 map of Mammoth Cave, drawn from memory, was so accurate that it remained in use for more than forty years?

elements.title: Jeff Malott (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Jeff Malott scored his first three goals for Cornell University on the same day?

elements.title: Angela Gallop (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that forensic scientist Angela Gallop has investigated the stomach contents of Diana, Princess of Wales, alleged alien abductions, and the presence of boar sperm in a hospital patient's intestines?
